                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Spent the weekend screwing around in Horizons.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.istaria.com" target="_blank">www.istaria.com</a>
<br />

<br />
After a FRUSTRATINGLY long 1Gig download...I signed up for my 7 day free trial and started.   Same High Fantasy style game as EQ with a few differences.  Yes there are your Humans, elves, gnomes and dwarves.  But there are also half-giants, Saris (Your Vahshir clone),  Sslik (Iskar clone),  Satyrs (Goat people!), Dryads (Yes you too can be a Tinkerbell), Fiends (Evil purple humans with horns and tails.)  and finally Dragons.  Yes I said you can BE a dragon.
<br />

<br />
Character creation is pretty slick.  Select the race and you're zipped down a long hallway to the room that contains your chosen race.  From there you can change the usual, faces, hair, colour etc and zoom in and out to see the changes.  Where it gets interesting is how you can change muscles and weight as well.   I created a dragon just to see what they looked like and they are treated a little differently as they don't wear items so seem to have much more flexibility in their customability.  You can change the head, scale pattern, chestplate pattern, spots pattern and the colour for all of those.  I ended up with a grey dragon with flourescent blue racing stripes and a streamlined head.  
<br />

<br />
Moving into the game I found it a little overwhelming but still familiar enough and am still getting used to the interface.  Of course some of this is from having to UNlearn 4 years of EQ controls.  You can customize the screen and move around all the windows and resize them and I ended up with a screen I could work with.  Mouse controls are important with right clicking mobs and NPC's happening often.  Keyboard shortcuts are changeable but not required as the setup they have used is pretty intuitive.  First person AND third person views are available.
<br />

<br />
The one thing I DO recommend is to look up the Options and find an entry called "Free Movement" and select it.  Otherwise when attacking your character becomes LOCKED running up to the mob your fighting.  I found this very annoying and it really bothered me when I was losing a fight and decided to run away.  Because my character was locked facing the mob I had to run away BACKWARDS.  I soon found that option and I now have full control of my character.  
<br />

<br />
Other windows and info provided in game adds alot.  For instance the guild management screen has several tabs and even allows for Points to be added to members that you can see in game.  The Search players window lets you search by almost anything, race, class, name, zone level etc.  Chat windows with NPC's give you links of text to click on instead of having you type the responses.  Basically click on the text you want to reply with and voila, you've just answered that phrase.  
<br />

<br />
Horizon's boasts a player based economy and there are basically 2 ways to play the game.  Adventure of Tradeskill your way.  Run around and kill monsters, or run around collecting raw materials and making stuff.  Softskins (Meaning non-dragons) can be both of these at the same time while dragons have to be one or the other for some reason.  I concentrated on Adventuring and had some fun killing maggots and little rat things and worked my way up to level 12 and killed some skeletons and zombies even.  I had an enjoyable time although I found the intelligence of some of the mobs to be a little strange but they did seem to get smarter as I leveled up a little.  I hope that once I get higher they will be really smart as I've heard great things about the Horizons AI.  
<br />

<br />
I was intending to be a caster Dragon and bought some spells and was confused on how to gain more magical knowledge when another dragon friend of mine informed me you can MAKE spells using the tradeskilling.  DOH!  So now I've gone back to learn some tradeskilling and have some recipies for things now that I am working on completing.  The interface is all window based and pretty intuitive.  Once I finish some items I'll let you know how that goes.  I'm stuck trying to figure out a tool requirement and can't seem to find one to buy so I might have to figure out how to make it instead.  
<br />

<br />
Definitely worth a look see if you like the old EQ feeling of being lost in a strange land and exploring with not much spoiler info out there.  Graphics are fantastic and they have kept pretty close to the high fantasy theme.  Don't think there are any dungeons yet or PvP but then again...I'm just a newb!!!  But out of all the MMORPG's I've tried recently this is one I've been the most impressed with so far.   Maybe see you in game if your 1Gig download finishes before my 7 days are up.  Haha.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ootpek Ubiqitous
<br />
ERTW!!! Enchanters Rule the World!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
